news.title: NGT asks central government to take action against UP housing board commissioner
news.para: According to its provisions, failure to comply with the NGT order can lead to a jail term of three years or a fine of up to Rs 10 crore. The green panel has sought a compliance report within two months.

news.title: UltraTech raises $500 million through sustainability-linked financing
news.para: Lenders for the transaction include Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corporation (SMBC), SBI, BNP Paribas, DBS, MUFG and Mizuho.

news.title: Godrej Interio to open 104 new stores, add over two lakh sq ft of retail space in FY25
news.para: Godrej Interio projects a 20 per cent growth this year and plans to add over 2 lakh sq ft of retail space in FY25. The company is poised to surpass 1,000 stores in August, it said in a statement.

news.title: Interarch Building Products' shares surge nearly 34% on Aug 26 in market debut
news.para: During the day, it zoomed 46.22 per cent to Rs 1,316. Shares of the firm ended at Rs 1,196.45, up 32.93 per cent.

news.title: EFC acquires 49,556 sq ft space in Pune for Rs 80 crore
news.para: EFC (I) has also incorporated a real estate investment trust (REIT) to established small and medium REIT the substantial corpus of Rs 499 crore.

news.title: Garuda Construction get Sebi's approval to float IPO
news.para: Garuda Construction and Engineering Ltd's proposed IPO is a combination of a fresh issue of 1.83 crore equity shares and an offer for sale of 95 lakh equity shares by promoter PKH Ventures Ltd.

news.title: Sebi's sustainability reporting boosts demand for green buildings: Colliers
news.para: As per the report, technology hub Bengaluru, and the country’s financial capital Mumbai recorded the highest green-certified building leasing, capturing around 75% of market share in the first half of 2024, with technology, engineering, and manufacturing firms showing a higher preference for leasing spaces in green-certified buildings.

news.title: HouseEazy raises $7 million in funding round led by Chiratae Ventures
news.para: The funds will be used to fuel the organisation's growth across new geographies in NCR, strengthening brand presence, team expansion and product enhancement, HouseEazy said.

news.title: Reliance Home Finance falls 4.93% on Aug 26 to hit lower circuit
news.para: Shares of Reliance Home Finance Ltd tumbled 4.93 per cent to Rs 4.24 -- the lowest trading permissible limit for the day.

news.title: Digitisation of land records using GIS to boost investments in residential projects
news.para: Digitisation will reduce uncertainty regarding the ownership of a property and boost early-stage investments in residential real estate projects, experts said.

news.title: Goa: Chimbel residents to oppose Unity mall
news.para: ​​The gram sabha members argued that the proposed location for the mall is “a wetland area adjacent to Chimbel lake”, which is considered ecologically fragile. They said that the site must be conserved and that no construction should be allowed.

news.title: UP-RERA informs allottees of five builders to file claims before IRP
news.para: UP-RERA has placed the pending complaints of the allottees as well as the proceedings of enforcement of its existing orders in ‘abeyance’.

news.title: Parts of Indore, Ujjain, Dewas & Dhar to form new metro city: Madhya Pradesh CM
news.para: Chief Minister Mohan Yadav announced the creation of a new metropolitan city by merging parts of Indore with Ujjain, Dewas, and Dhar districts. At the Kabuli Chana Traders Association meet, he emphasized the state's focus on commerce and trade, highlighting initiatives in the food processing sector and efforts to support chickpea cultivation and export.

news.title: Mumbai: Adani Group struggles to secure land to rehabilitate Dharavi residents
news.para: Only those who lived in Dharavi before the year 2000 will get free homes in the redevelopment and a lot of the land needed to rehabilitate people - at least 580 acres for now - will be to provide housing to the roughly 700,000 people considered ineligible.

news.title: Goa: GIDC to shift most of its services online
news.para: The new e-governance system, built on an open-source platform called DIGIT, promises to reduce the number of documents and the time frame for all approvals by over 60%. The new system is likely to be launched on Sep 5.

news.title: Haryana RERA orders OSB Expressway Towers' builder to complete project in six months
news.para: The H-Rera met with homebuyers regarding the delayed OSB Expressway Towers project in Sector 109, Gurgaon, and issued a final warning. If the project isn't completed in six months, control may transfer to a buyers' association or involve a third-party builder. This action aims to protect buyers who've waited over seven years for their homes.

news.title: Builders in Uttar Pradesh who accepted rehabilitation deal but didn’t pay advance may lose land
news.para: Officials said Noida Authority was planning a three-pronged action – cancelling the lease deeds of defaulter projects, seizing land lying idle and taking over unsold inventory.

news.title: Delhi HC seeks status report on probe into Signature View Apartment lapses
news.para: The court asked the land-owning agency for an update after examining a letter sent to it by CBI in March last year, asking for certain details and a copy of a vigilance inquiry ordered by the lieutenant governor earlier.

news.title: NCDRC issues non-bailable warrant against Mantri Developers' founder
news.para: According to the order issued by the NCDRC on January 31, 2022, Mantri Estate Management Private Limited and others had collected Rs 7,12,86,650 from 302 flat owners.

news.title: FPCE writes to centre questioning MahaRERA move to set up forum to settle builder-buyer dispute
news.para: ​Forum for People's Collective Efforts' (FPCE) President Abhay Upadhyay has written a letter on August 19 to Union Ministry of Housing and Urban Affairs Additional Secretary Satinder Pal Singh objecting to the conciliation forum constituted by MahaRERA and its "suspicious functioning".
